OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,F"Namely that there was no adequate
OL,8,Fguidance to staff to follow a patient
OL,9,Fseen to abscond from the ward."
OL,11,FEllame had been under 24-hour one-to-
OL,12,Fone supervision by a registered mental
OL,13,Fhealth nurse on an acute ward at
OL,14,FWorthing Hospital when she absconded.
OL,16,FShe was on that ward because there was
OL,17,F"no alternative" and no adequate bed
OL,18,Ffor her risk level was available, the
OL,19,Fcourt heard.
