OL,7,F"They didn't have the resources or the
OL,8,Fskills to properly support Ellame but
OL,9,Fthe alternative was refusing her,"
OL,10,Fsaid Eleanor Sanderson, defending UHST.
OL,12,FHer mother, Nancy Ford-Dunn described
OL,13,FEllame as a "loving and supportive big
OL,14,Fsister" who was very creative and
OL,15,Floved art and dancing.
OL,17,FIn her victim impact statement, she
OL,18,Fsaid: "She was loved so very deeply,
OL,19,Fwe miss her more than words can
OL,20,Fexpress,
