OL,7,F"Colleagues involved in her care are
OL,8,Fdevastated by her death, and the
OL,9,Fimpact it continues to have on her
OL,10,Ffamily and friends.
OL,12,F"Everyone accepts that people with
OL,13,Facute mental illness should not be in
OL,14,Fgeneral hospital wards or A&E
OL,15,Fdepartments, but we had a
OL,16,Fresponsibility to protect her while
OL,17,Fshe was in our care, and we offer our
OL,18,Fheartfelt apologies for not being able
OL,19,Fto do that.
